This directory contains some patches for various programs to optimize
use in conjunction with mgetty+sendfax.

For a detailed description, look into the files. The first few lines
usually describe it.

If you have questions, ask the author of the patch!

gert
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
pbmtext.iso-p

make PBMTEXT capable of "printing" ISO 8859-1 capable characters.
Unfortunately, I do not have any font files for it yet.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
dip337.p1

repair locking with the original DIP 3.3.7 version (Linux) [not dip-uri!]
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
ecu320.p1

repair utmp handling with ECU 3.20 (can't dial out while mgetty is active)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
gslp.ps-iso.p

make GNU/Aladdin's Ghostscript 3.x accept ISO 8859-1 umlauts in "gslp.ps".
Thus, you can fax ascii texts with umlauts with "faxspool".
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
pbmtog3.p1

Fix for PBMPLUS' pbmtog3 ptogram. Without this patch, the G3 files created
are not valid T.4 data, and most fax receivers will reject them.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
pnmtops.p1

Make independent scaling in X- and Y-directon possible with PBMPLUS'
pnmtops program.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
taylor104.p1

Patch for Taylor UUCP 1.04 to make setting of the username (when using
taylor passwd files) possible with "-L".
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
